Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%tsp}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} or #rolling pin{} until it's 1-2cm thick.

Put the @plain flour{2%tbsp} in a large #bowl{} with a good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together. Add the chicken to the bowl, then toss to ensure an even coating of flour.

Repeat for the other breast(s). Discard any remaining flour left in the bowl.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, lay in the chicken. Fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a board lined with #kitchen paper{} and set aside.

In a medium bowl, mix together the @tomato puree{30%g}, @sugar{1/4%tsp} and a splash of @water{splash} - just enough to loosen the mixture to a spreadable consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Lay your fried chicken onto a medium baking tray and spread the tomato sauce evenly over the top.

Top with the grated Cheddar, then bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the cheese has melted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @glazed burger bun{2}, then pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, pop the burger buns on your plates and spread the cut sides with the @fresh pesto{32%g}.

Stack the fried chicken on the bun bases, then top with some @wild rocket{20%g} and the bun lids.

Serve with your herby fries and any remaining rocket alongside. Enjoy!